Santa J. Ono is a Canadian-American biologist and academic administrator who has served as President and Vice Chancellor of the University of British Columbia (UBC) since 2016. Prior to joining UBC, he served as President of the University of Cincinnati from 2012 to 2016.

Born in Vancouver, Canada in 1962, Ono earned his undergraduate degree from the University of Chicago and his Ph.D. in experimental medicine from McGill University. He is a renowned researcher in the field of immunology, with expertise in the areas of eye diseases and allergic inflammation.

In addition to his research accomplishments, Ono has also been recognized for his leadership in higher education. He has been a strong advocate for issues such as student mental health and academic freedom, and he has been active in promoting diversity and inclusion on university campuses.